### Managerial Interpretation

The dashboard suggests that subscription success is not evenly distributed across all customers or campaign conditions. Marketing managers should avoid treating the entire customer list the same way. Instead, they can improve campaign efficiency by prioritizing customer segments and campaign settings that show stronger subscription rates.

Key recommendations:

- Prioritize customer groups with stronger historical subscription rates.
- Use job category, age group, contact type, and previous campaign outcome as targeting signals.
- Consider campaign timing because response rates vary by month.
- Be careful when using call duration for prediction because it is only known after the contact happens.
- Use economic indicators as context when evaluating campaign performance.
